snippet.textDisplay: The actual point everyone's missing out is that Bangladesh is a multilingual country. 'Bangla' as a whole neither represents Bangladesh nor its diversity. Do not consider everything from a business perspective. For the WB singers, they've their own platforms in India. We should focus on branding of our own country. Also there is no geographical region called 'Bangla' in today's world, only one independent country that primarily represents the bengali culture or language to the world is also Bangladesh.
